### Test — `--fast` subsample + concise output
Use the `fast` fixture from `tests/conftest.py`. Report max err + index + pass rate, never raw arrays. Make the assert message greppable.
```python
def test_logp_vs_reference(fast, ref_smiles):
    """Crippen logP vs published values; --fast = every 10th molecule."""
    data = ref_smiles[::10] if fast else ref_smiles
    errs = [abs(MolLogP(Chem.MolFromSmiles(s)) - p) for s, p in data]
    n_pass = sum(e < 0.1 for e in errs)
    assert n_pass == len(errs), (
        f"logp: max err {max(errs):.3f} at idx {errs.index(max(errs))} "
        f"({n_pass}/{len(errs)} pass <0.1)"
    )
```

